73
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,200
 Do you have a flu?

74
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:59,760
 Is your platelets count is decreasing?

75
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:08,560
 So the other symptoms which are really very important for you

76
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:15,440
 as a medical petitioner to decide whether the person is a COVID patient or not a COVID patient.

77
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:22,000
 So of course, if somebody is just saying I'm feeling pain and I have fever,

78
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:26,080
 it could be a malaria, it could be a typhoid, it could be a dengue fever.

79
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:29,280
 It could be a normal seasonal flu.

80
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:36,480
 So it is very important for that medical petitioner to identify,

81
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:39,760
 to learn the features which are very important

82
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:44,480
 to distinguish between the related diseases, which I just mentioned.

83
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:52,720
 So maybe your model hasn't learned those features properly, which are very important.

84
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:57,200
 And that is what we are saying the model is underfitted.

85
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:59,440
 It did not learn the things properly.

86
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:03,280
 The second one is overfitting.

87
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:10,720
 Overfitting happens when the model learns too much from the training data, including the noise.

88
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:15,840
 It means some things which is really very important for you to learn

89
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:22,560
 to distinguish that this is right, this is wrong, right?

90
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:29,200
 You also considered that noise, that wrong things into your training,

91
00:09:29,200 --> 00:09:31,760
 and you consider them that this is okay.

92
00:09:32,560 --> 00:09:35,600
 There is no issue with that one, right?

93
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:37,840
 And what happens then?

94
00:09:37,840 --> 00:09:47,680
 So sometimes maybe this example may not be applicable or understandable to everyone,

95
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:55,680
 but sometimes there are few words which normally we don't want to speak with our family members,

96
00:09:55,680 --> 00:10:00,880
 especially with the parents, especially with our siblings, for example.

97
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:08,880
 And there are certain jokes, certain fun things which we normally do with our friends, right?

98
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:17,600
 And if in your brought up, in our brought up, if we think that this is okay to do,

99
00:10:18,560 --> 00:10:25,360
 whether the jokes which could be done with the friends or the fun which could be done

100
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:31,920
 with the family is totally different or there is a certain limit, right?

101
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:36,400
 Something which you can do with your friends, but not with your parents, for example.

102
00:10:36,960 --> 00:10:41,440
 But if you understood that this is okay, both things are okay.

103
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:43,360
 So now what will happen?

104
00:10:43,360 --> 00:10:46,160
 It means you learned the noise as well.

105
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:49,280
 You learned the wrong things as well.

106
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:56,320
 And why I'm saying it is noise, because this is not applicable to those jokes,

107
00:10:56,320 --> 00:11:02,800
 are not applicable to your parents, but you consider them as it's okay, right?

108
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:06,560
 And you haven't distinguished them properly.

109
00:11:07,360 --> 00:11:09,920
 Now what will happen when you go home?

110
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:14,400
 You talk with your parents, you talk with your siblings.

111
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:18,080
 Maybe you will make those jokes with them.

112
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:20,080
 Right?

113
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:24,000
 Without understanding that these are not applicable to them.

114
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:30,560
 So that is what they call it as you are overfitted.

115
00:11:31,360 --> 00:11:36,960
 So overfitted happens when the model learns too much from the training data,

116
00:11:38,480 --> 00:11:42,000
 including the noise and outliers.

117
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:45,920
 Means some things which like you have to distinguish it clearly.

118
00:11:46,640 --> 00:11:53,360
 And it performs very well on the training data, but poorly on the test data.

119
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:53,680
 Right?

120
00:11:53,680 --> 00:11:56,640
 Because you have learned the noise as well.

121
00:11:57,280 --> 00:12:06,160
 Now what will happen if somebody say is this joke is applicable to your parents or just your friends?

122
00:12:06,720 --> 00:12:09,440
 You're not able to distinguish it properly.

123
00:12:09,440 --> 00:12:10,160
 Right?

124
00:12:10,160 --> 00:12:12,880
 Because you considered everything is okay.

125
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,080
 Right?

126
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:20,640
 Now if somebody give you a test data because now they have the right data, that is correct.

127
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:20,880
 Right?

128
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:21,760
 This is okay.

129
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:23,360
 This is not okay.

130
00:12:23,360 --> 00:12:24,160
 Right?

131
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:29,120
 So but when the test data will come, you will not really perform good there.

132
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:29,440
 Right?

133
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:32,080
 And that is what it is overfitted.

134
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:37,600
 Overfitted happens due to the model is too complex, too many features,

135
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:41,680
 are very little data, are very high, various is there.

136
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:44,020
 Right?

137
00:12:44,720 --> 00:12:47,680
 These two things are really very important.

138
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:54,400
 Underfitting is when your model fails to learn the important features, important patterns,

139
00:12:55,040 --> 00:13:01,120
 important information, hidden information that a model, a machine learning algorithm has to learn.

140
00:13:02,080 --> 00:13:04,640
 And it hasn't learned it properly.

141
00:13:04,640 --> 00:13:11,840
 So now even if you will give the training data or the testing data, it will not perform good there.

142
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:18,800
 And on the other hand, overfitting is when your model is learned too much from the training data,

143
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:19,600
 even the noise.

144
00:13:20,240 --> 00:13:25,360
 And now when it is applicable to the test data, it is not performing really well there.

145
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,720
 Right?

146
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:31,360
 And that is what we call it as overfitting and underfitting.

