155
00:14:06,880 --> 00:14:11,600
 But the algorithm for classification as part of this course.

156
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:18,160
 We discussed in our last class that classification is a supervised learning technique.

157
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:24,560
 Supervised learning means where we know what we are going to do, means we know our label.

158
00:14:25,280 --> 00:14:31,840
 And classification because the type of the label, the type of the attribute,

159
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:35,520
 which we are going to predict is categorical in nature.

160
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:41,440
 It has few categories among which you have to do that classification, that prediction.

161
00:14:42,240 --> 00:14:49,360
 And then we further discussed, if there are only two outcomes for a particular label,

162
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:52,400
 then we call it as binary classification.

163
00:14:52,400 --> 00:15:00,400
 And if it has more than two classes, more than two outcome values of that particular label,

164
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:05,680
 among which we have to do the prediction, then it is called multi-class classification.

165
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:12,800
 With a very simple example, and if the type of the attribute is continuous,

166
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:16,800
 then it is a regression problem.

167
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:22,560
 And with very simple example, I can explain these three concepts.

168
00:15:22,560 --> 00:15:24,560
 That is the weather forecast data.

169
00:15:25,200 --> 00:15:32,320
 If you are saying tomorrow is rainy or not rainy, then it means,

170
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:36,800
 firstly, it is a supervised learning, means you know what you are going to do.

171
00:15:37,600 --> 00:15:46,160
 Now, you just have to predict between which whether tomorrow is going to be rain or not, right?

172
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:52,640
 Then it is a classification and it is a binary classification, right?

173
00:15:52,640 --> 00:15:59,520
 Now, if the classes are whether tomorrow is rainy, windy, cloudy.

174
00:16:00,560 --> 00:16:06,880
 Again, you know what you are going to do and the type are the limited,

175
00:16:06,880 --> 00:16:11,280
 but it is more than two, then it is multi-class classification.

176
00:16:12,880 --> 00:16:17,280
 If you are predicting, how much would be the temperature tomorrow?

177
00:16:18,640 --> 00:16:24,320
 7 degree, 8 degree, 9 degree regression, because the value

178
00:16:24,320 --> 00:16:28,640
 which you are going to predict is continuous in nature, right?

179
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:32,560
 Then we started with the decision tree.

180
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:39,760
 We discussed that decision tree is basically used for classification

181
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:43,200
 and also decision tree regressor, DTR.

182
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:50,400
 And we discussed that in this one, you have attribute features to be selected.

183
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:56,320
 And the first feature that you will select on the top is would be the your root attribute.

184
00:16:57,040 --> 00:17:03,200
 And then the branches would be the outcome values of that particular attribute.

185
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:07,600
 And then once you reach here, you will basically need to

186
00:17:07,600 --> 00:17:14,720
 split your data based on these features and here there would be a separate split based on this

187
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:21,840
 feature value and then you will keep growing this tree means it is a recursive process

188
00:17:21,840 --> 00:17:25,040
 until you reach on your leaf node, right?

189
00:17:25,760 --> 00:17:34,720
 And then further we discussed that if there would be any value here, which we can just answer.

190
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:42,320
 And that is what the decision tree algorithm is also called is rule based learning.

191
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:51,120
 Right, rule based learning where you induce certain rules after constructing a decision tree

192
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:53,360
 and then you can just simply answer.

193
00:17:53,360 --> 00:17:58,960
 So, for example, you can make one rule that if the student value is no,

194
00:17:58,960 --> 00:18:02,800
 income value is high, age value is less than 30.

195
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:10,560
 So, you would say no, you can have another rule student value is no, income value is high,

196
00:18:10,560 --> 00:18:16,080
 but the age is greater than 30, then you will approve the loan for that particular person.

197
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:18,320
 Right?

198
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:26,080
 So, means you will write all those rules which you have induced inferred from this decision tree.

199
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:35,680
 Right? Now, before revising, how this decision tree would be constructed because then I have

200
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:41,520
 to come back here, I want to link the limitations which you have mentioned.

201
00:18:43,600 --> 00:18:43,920
 Right?

202
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:52,240
 So, you can see that if you have more number of attributes, then it would be really hard

203
00:18:52,240 --> 00:18:58,080
 for you to manage the whole construction of this decision tree into your memory.

204
00:18:58,880 --> 00:19:06,320
 Or if you will store it, you need a substantial amount of memory to store this whole decision tree.

205
00:19:07,840 --> 00:19:08,080
 Right?

