 But what are the chances?

218
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:26,800
 How much sure you are?

219
00:20:27,520 --> 00:20:33,440
 What is the probability that you will not approve the loan for that particular person?

220
00:20:35,360 --> 00:20:44,320
 Right? Because when we talk about classification, we need a certain answers.

221
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:54,000
 Sometimes you have a line on 50 and somebody is on 48, somebody is on 52.

222
00:20:54,960 --> 00:21:05,200
 So, there are very high chances that 52, 54th one will jump into that class below 50.

223
00:21:05,920 --> 00:21:13,360
 And that 48 would adjust a normal change into the feature, can jump into the 52.

224
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:19,840
 But we are 100% sure if somebody is on 20, if somebody is on 80.

225
00:21:21,040 --> 00:21:30,720
 81 is 100% pass, 21 is 100% fail, 48 one can pass, 52 one can be fail.

226
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:37,760
 So, 20, 81 is okay, 70, 31 is okay.

227
00:21:37,760 --> 00:21:40,880
 But the border cases creates a lot of problem.

228
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:46,800
 For that one, we need to have a shorty, we need to know the probability.

